<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3462] default closure parameter causes BUG! exception in phase &apos;class generation&apos;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3462</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I&apos;m calling the following closure making the range of days of a month:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;test.gr&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;month = { &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; date = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date().format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;yyyyMM&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) -&amp;gt;
    GregorianCalendar.instance.with {
        time = Date.parse(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;yyyyMM&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, date)
        (time .. time+(getActualMaximum(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH)-1))
    }
}

month(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;200101&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m getting the following exception: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caught: BUG! exception in phase &apos;class generation&apos; in source unit &apos;C:\Groovy\test.gr&apos; ClassNode#getTypeClass for Date is called before the type class is set&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I&apos;m making the same in method:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def getDays(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; date = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date().format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;yyyyMM&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) {
 ...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;everything works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tried both 1.6.1 and 1.6&lt;/p&gt;</description>
